ption, providing a fascinating account of an early bestseller's incarnations over 250 years of literary history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aBooks and readingzEnglandxHistoryy16th century. 0aBooks and readingzEnglandxHistoryy17th century. 0aHousehold employees in literature. 0aPopular culturezEnglandxHistory. 0aPopular literaturezEnglandxHistory and criticism. 0aRomancesxAppreciationzEnglandxHistory. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCUP eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066254208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044247208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311045952440uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/newc12378423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231504850.jpg  a978-3-11-044247-2  CUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013  a978-3-11-045952-4  CUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066254-2  CUP eBook Package 2000-2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG